<https://w3id.org/bench4ke/metric/MeanCosineSimilarity> a dqv:Metric, ftr:Test ;
    dcterms:identifier "https://w3id.org/bench4ke/metric/MeanCosineSimilarity" ;
    dcterms:title      "Mean Cosine Similarity"@en ;
    rdfs:label         "MeanCosineSimilarity: average pairwise cosine similarity across all generated–gold CQ pairs"^^xsd:string ;
    dcat:version       "0.1.0"^^xsd:string ;
    ftr:status         "Active"@en ;
    dcat:landingPage   <https://w3id.org/bench4ke/metric/MeanCosineSimilarity> ;
    dcterms:description """Mean Cosine Similarity computes the cosine similarity between the SBERT sentence embeddings of every
generated CQ and every gold-standard CQ, then reports the mean over all |generated| × |gold| pairs.

Embeddings are produced by the all-MiniLM-L6-v2 model from the sentence-transformers library, which
maps CQ text to a 384-dimensional dense vector capturing sentence-level semantics.

Formula (for sets G of generated CQs and M of gold CQs):
  score = mean_{g ∈ G, m ∈ M} cos(embed(g), embed(m))

Range: [0, 1]. Provides a global distributional view of alignment between the two CQ sets.
Because it averages over all pairs — including non-best-matching ones — it is typically lower than
best-match aggregations and reflects overall topical overlap rather than coverage."""@en ;
    dcat:keyword       "Metric"@en,
    "Cosine Similarity"@en,
    "SBERT"@en,
    "Semantic Similarity"@en,
    "Bench4KE"@en ;
    dqv:inDimension    <https://w3id.org/bench4ke/dimension/SemanticSimilarity> ;
    dcterms:isPartOf   <https://w3id.org/bench4ke/task/CQGeneration> ;
    rdfs:seeAlso    <https://w3id.org/cq4oe/metric/SemanticCosineSimilarity> ;
    ftr:hasBenchmark   <https://w3id.org/bench4ke> ;
    ftr:supportedBy    <https://w3id.org/bench4ke> ;
    dpv:isApplicableFor <https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q184754> ;
    dcterms:creator    <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0266-3452> ;
    dcat:contactPoint  <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0266-3452> ;
    dcterms:publisher  <https://w3id.org/bench4ke/org/unibo> ;
    dcterms:license    <http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/> .

